Zak Stein:

 "We are systematically and intentionally 
  misinformed
  and provided only with 
  *munitions of the mind*
   - useful for in-group/out-group boundaries 
   - useless for actually reasoned
      evidence-based conversation. 

 If you believe your media outlets
  are the exception to this
  then you are captured
  and will start posting links 
  studies and articles
  as if it really matters
  like you might get someone
  to realise the "truth." 

 Yes, please tell me about 
  the pre-prints and studies you read
  in fields you are not expert in
  - where the replication crisis runs rampant 
  - where the wrong incentives 
     for knowledge production
     have been endemic for decades.  

 Neurotic resistance to accepting the reality
  of our actual epistemic position
  results in righteous certainty
  about things where certainty is not possible.   

 There can be no closure 
  through reasoned "debate" 
  due to absence of actual knowledge.
   -Yet we believe it is our duty to argue 
      and convince others 
      of things we actually know very little about.

 The result is escalating
  frustrations and eventually violence
  as reason fails
  again and again
  due to the impossibility 
  of the discursive situation itself. 

 This double-bind 
  of placement in impossibile discursive situation
  with demand for resolution through discourse
  is part of the structure 
  of the genocidal grammar
  leading us to believe 
  that those we disagree with
  are acting in bad faith
  because the truth is easy to see
  simple and clear, 
     -why won't they simply face the facts!?! 

 Our sense that the disagrable  
  are incorrigible 
  and willfully negligent
  of obvious truths
  means that the only recourse
  is physical coercion.

 We must not talk ourselves 
  into the traps set for us.

 Instead we should start to talk 
  about the traps themselves
  about the those who designed them
  about the known and well documented
    ascendancy of behavioral sciences 
    in the design of digital media 
    wedded to decades old propaganda machines 
     now made capable of *undue influence.*  
 
 We must find ways
  to undue the spellbinding trance 
  of the genocidal grammar
  we are being forced to speak."

